The paper discusses security and privacy protection mechanisms in aggregation protocols used in wireless sensor networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also discusses various existing protocols for secure aggregation in WSN, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The proposed protocol for secure aggregation also involves machine learning techniques for detecting false data injected by malicious nodes, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE).
